
---


@startuml

' Classes
class WebPortal {
  - version: String
  - url: String
}

class Building {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - energyClass: String (A/B/C/D)
  - address: String
  - yearOfConstruction: Integer
  - owner: User
  - additionalEntries: List<Entry>
  - images: List<Image>
  - profilePhoto: Image
}

class Entry {
  - name: String
  - isPublic: Boolean
  + addEntry()
  + updateEntry()
  + deleteEntry()
}

class TextualEntry <|-- Entry
class NumericEntry <|-- Entry

TextualEntry {
  - content: String
}

NumericEntry {
  - value: Float
  - unit: String
}

class Image {
  - fileName: String
}

class User {
  - username: String
  - email: String
  - password: String
  - buildings: List<Building>
  - comments: List<Comment>
}

class Administrator <|-- User
Administrator {
  - idCardNumber: String
}

class Comment {
  - content: String
  - author: User
  - building: Building
  - date: DateTime
}

class Search {
  + searchBuildings(keyword: String): List<Building>
}

' Relationships
WebPortal "1" -- "0..*" Building : contains
User "1" -- "0..*" Building : owns
Building "1" -- "0..*" Entry : has
Building "1" -- "0..*" Image : has
Entry "1" -- "0..*" TextualEntry : type
Entry "1" -- "0..*" NumericEntry : type
User "1" -- "0..*" Comment : creates
Comment "1" -- "1" Building : belongs to
Comment "1" -- "1" User : posted by
User "1" -- "0..*" Search : uses
Administrator "1" -- "0..*" User : manages

@enduml

---

### đź“‹ **Use Cases & Actors**

Here are **10 meaningful use cases**, associated with **actors**, using **generalization** where applicable:

@startuml

actor Visitor
actor User
actor Administrator

Visitor --> (Search for Buildings)
User --> (Register as User)
User --> (Login)
User --> (Create Building)
User --> (Add Additional Entry to Building)
User --> (Comment on Building)
User --> (View Public Entries)
Administrator --> (Setup User Account)
Administrator --> (Delete Comment)
User --> (Manage Entries)

' Generalizations
User <|-- Visitor
User <|-- Administrator

@enduml

---

### đź”Ť **Explanation of Key Elements**

- **Generalization**:
  - `User` is generalized into `Visitor` and `Administrator`.
  - `Entry` is generalized into `TextualEntry` and `NumericEntry`.

- **Associations**:
  - A `WebPortal` contains multiple `Building`s.
  - A `User` owns multiple `Building`s.
  - A `Building` has multiple `Entry`s and `Image`s.
  - An `Entry` can be either `TextualEntry` or `NumericEntry`.
  - A `User` can create `Comments`, which are linked to specific `Building`s.

- **Use Case Hierarchy**:
  - `User` and `Administrator` inherit some use cases from `Visitor`, but have more specific actions like `Setup User Account` or `Delete Comment`.

